block.comment: Sets the rocket sprites starting point to centre stage.
This Section sets the starting variables.
timetoTravel variable is the time it takes the asteroid to travel across the screens starting value
dodge counter variable tracks how many passes the rocket makes across the screen starting at zero.
Create a copy of the asteroid sprite for its next pass
This Section sets the roation speed and frequency of the Asteroid
"spinningspeed" variable randomly picks number of degrees the asteroid sprites will rotate.
Asteroid sprite will rotate "spinningspeed" every 0.05 seconds
spinningspeed for the for for the amount of rotation
This Section controls the travel path of the Asteroid and the speed that it takes to do it.
Asteroid starting point from the top of the screen randomly between -350 and 350 for the of value of "x" and the fixed value of 350 "y"
Asteroid sprites finishing point at the bottom of the screen randomly picked between -350 and 350 for "x" and -350 for "y" in the the time timetoTravel variable in seconds is set to.
dodgecounter increases on the completion of the asteroid travelling down the screen from top to bottom.
if the dodgeCounter gets to 3 the time to travel reduces to go 5 seconds to cross the screen.
Make a copy of the asteroid sprite with the new condions
